so the past week has been so mixed up i don't even feel like re-explaining everything, but here goes the something.  

so i've been waiting for Monday, August 28, 2006, ever since Monday, March 15, 2006, and now that the day has come and gone i can truthfully say that it was one of the worst days ever.  i get on campus and b4 i can even think of enjoying the fact that school is starting i have a major nosebleed.  then after that one stops...i have another the only difference is that the second time i was coughing up blood clots (fun right??).  so i went to the ER for like the first time ever.  the short version i went to the ER just about everyday for 4 days.  it was a nightmare, but now i'm feeling better...now i can stress over other stuff.  

since i was feeling better by friday i decided to dress the part.  since i have a nice amount of new clothes i picked out a really nice outfit.  i got a lot of comments about it, but not from the ppl i expected...it was a lil weird.  so i went to dodgeball and it was packed.  i have missed it so much over the summer.  it was all i talked about on friday nights whether i was doing something or not.  even when i was at church i would say things like "if i was at school after i leave here i could go play dodgeball."  it amuzed ppl a lot.  it was so weird tho to have that many ppl there.  it wasn't until it got close to 3 that it started looking normal again.  we, as in my lil group, had one accident.  tammy got hit in the face and her glasses broke, but she's ok.  i didn't get back to my room until like 5am cuz we started talking to campo.  he was pretty cool and it was funny cuz he knows lynn from high school.  i finally rolled off to bed around 6 or so.  

the past couple days have been kinda weird in general tho.  i mean besides the obvious ppl have been acting different.  i mean just random stuff and listening to other ppl trying to figure the random acts out isn't helping either.  i really just wish that ppl knew how to give straight answers.  i don't understand y it's so hard for them to just say what they mean.  don't they know that most ppl can't stand that crap.  i know i for 1 am sick of stressing over some of the stupidest things in the world.  the really messed up part is the fact that if u even think of trying to figure ppl out and then label them as such they get so offended.  even tho they're offended they still refuse to help u understand..they would just rather complain that u don't understand them and then they still give u vague answers to ur questions and then run around and do stupid stuff.  i don't c a point in trying to please everyone anymore.  i give up on it in fact.  i'm gonna b me and if u can't handle that then i guess this "friendship" as u might call it is officially over.

so this weekend was just....amazing to say the least.  my dad took me and my best friend to atlantic city.  i've been b4, but i didn't get to take anyone and she's never been to jersey so i knew we were in for a good time.  

we had a blast!!!!  my dad and i left work early friday (MY LAST DAY OF WORK :-D!!!!) and i picked up ashley and a limo came and picked us up and took us up there.  "unfortunately" my dad couldn't get 2 rooms in the same hotel, since everything was booked up b/c of the concert and the tournaments, so he and his girl stayed on one side of the island and me and my friend stayed on the other.  we ordered so much room service and like 3 movies and we had amazing beds.  my friend wanted to steal the beds.  

friday night we just stayed in and had room service for dinner and watched a movie.  my dad had a round one game for one of the tournaments he was playing in so he came by later.  after they left ash and i wanted to go to the gym or the pool of something, but everything (except the casino of course) closed early (it was like 12).  the outdoor pool closed at 7, the gym/spa closed as 8 and the arcade closed 10.  so we wound up just going back to our room and watching another movie.  we went to sleep around 4am.  

saturday we woke up and got dressed and then went to the arcade until my dad called.  we took a jittney (the bus of ac) to the outlets and then his girlfriend took me shopping on my dads dime.  IT WAS GREAT!!!! i bought so many outfits i can't wait to get to school to show everyone.  ash and i got a matching hoodie so we look like twins...not really, but ok lol.  after we finished shopping we went and ate and then ash and i headed for the boardwalk.  we hung out at the carnival for a while and then my dad calls me and tells me that he got 2 more tickets to the concert if we wanted to go.  so went to the mariah carey show that night.  it was pretty good and we had good seats.  we got some souvenirs and then took the jitney back to our hotel.  we watched another movie and ordered more room service and then went to sleep around 3am.  

sunday we were suppose to meet my dad for brunch at 11, but we didn't make it there until 12 and he was kinda pissed.  we ate and then he went off to play some more while me, ash and his girl hit the boardwalk.  we went to the ripley's believe it or not museum which was very entertaining.  then ash bought some shirts for her family and some taffy.  as we started to head back to the hotel since we were suppose to leave at 4 and it was getting close my dads girl slipped off and picked up a gift for me from my dad.  it was my name in blue animals and figures.  it's hard to explain, but if u've seen them b4 u know what i'm talking about.  i'm bringing it to school so erry1 can c it.  we finally left around 5.  we hit some traffic, and we made it back by 10 or so.  

it really was the perfect end to a not too exciting summer.  now i'm counting down the days until school and since i'm not working this week i know it's going to go by extremely fast and i can't wait :-D.

2day was the 1st, and with every new month it seems that something new happens.  this month, however, the "new" thing that happened didn't happen to me.  one of my very good friends from high school and one of my original white sisters got married.  as i was getting ready for the wedding i realized that unlike Lorelai i am not at the age where i can be "depressed" that my friend who is younger than me is getting married b4 me.  i am at the age, however, where i can only ask the question WHY??  i don't understand why she wanted to get married so young.  i mean she just graduated from high school and she's not even 18 yet.  i guess they must have rushed b/c he's going in the military in a few weeks and then he might get shipped to germany, but still i can't help but feel that it's a big mistake.  nonetheless, i am one of her closest friends so i'm supporting her decision and just being there for her.  i've already told her that i'm giving her a week (aka her honeymoon) and then i want to hear from here every night...or at least once a week.

so it's been a while.  i don't understand it, but whenever i get back home i alwayz seem to never write.  i alwayz tell myself i'm going to, but then i never do.  so obviously i'm at home.  i was going to write about rockbridge and the amazing time i had, but i don't feel like it mayb another time.  it must be the house *shrug*.  i'm just going to start with since i've gotten back.  

so i've been back here in MD for over two weeks now.  i've been to see just about everyone i think by week no. 1.  the first week back i spent getting job apps and b4 anyone asks i don't know if i'm getting my old job back.  i won't know until sometime in June and we don't think that i will.  last week i spent hanging out mainly.  my dad left to go on a cruise with his little young thing and left me here to dog sit, which by the way sucks.  this dog hates me and never listens to me.  we do have our good times though.  

i've been spending a lot of time with my bestest bud Ashely.  we've been hanging out on every off day she has for the past 2 weeks.  she's been helping me get a job and shop and everything.  we and my cuzin went and saw X-Men III (which by the way is frickin' awesome!!!!!!!! and i can't wait to go c it again) and she spent the night.  i'm having a bit of a cash flow problem, mainly b/c of all the money i spent on ppl during the school year, but i don't regret any of it...even the stuff i bought for "him".  so Ashley has been paying for just about everything for me.  it kinda sucks cause i know she's doing it just b/c she can which is what i told everyone all year long, but it's different with her b/c i know her situation and i don't really like taking money from her but she's as stubborn as me and won't take no for an answer.  so we've been spending so much time together that her mom actually said that she can't hang out with me for a week.  it's actually quite funny though.  

i've been taking a break from being online if anyone has noticed or cared and it's actually a good thing.  only a few of you might actually understand what this means.  instead of having thoughts and dreams i only have dreams.  now i just gotta find a way to get rid of those too and i'll b great :-\.  i'm sure that once i start working i'll b fine.  oh yeah, i got a job at bath and body works.  i've already done 2 days of orientation which is the only really hard part.  i had to sit still for 3hrs or so in a cold storage room watching "informative" videos and filling out papers about them.  my next day of work i'm going to get floor and register training.  i'm actually really looking forward to working there.  it seems like something that i'd b really good at.  even though i really wanted to b a waitress instead B&B was the first place to call back.  

it's kinda weird but i really can't wait to get back to school and not for the same reason as everyone else either.  i actually can't wait until classes start even though i have a hard class and work load.  i think it's b/c last semester i barely passed and that is not me.  i think i can't wait for next semester b/c i want to regain my good name as a student.  i do miss ppl.  i mean i miss ppl a lot, but the ones i miss the most i talk to on the phone all the time...i mean my minute counts r at like 1600 and 2000...i talk to them a lot :-D.  the one(s) i don't or can't talk to i know that if i really wanted to talk to them i could or if they really wanted to talk to me they could so i'm not that worried about that.  

i think i've made this long enough that only my bordest and/or goodest friends will actually read all of it and/or comment so yeah...until i'm bored enough to write again.  peace.

the drag ball was so much fun!!  the ppl there were all so pretty!!  their outfits were to die for and their shoes were amazing!!...and the prizes.  setting up was fun.  all we mainly did was cover up the windows and glasses of the "dressing room" for the queens and we put crepe paper on the stage as a replacement for the lack of a skirt.  prior to the the show we (tammy, kayla and i) got to meet the mc ashley.  we talked with her for a while about tons of random things.  since we were setting up well past the time the commons closed we ordered chinese food for dinner.  

the turn out was great.  there was a lot of ppl there.  the prizes were very entertaining to watch ppl win.  when the show first started kayla said it would b funny if i won the thing she has been planning on buying me as a gag present, which was a vibrator.  the first one that was up guess who won...the girl that has never won anything up until now.  when they called the number i knew it was mine...then when i looked at my ticket i was sure that it was mine.  it was even better when i got up there and ashley was telling the audience a little bit about our conversations earlier.  he was saying how kayla and i were comparing our boobs again.  don't ask me how it came up, but i know kayla brought it up earlier and ashley felt the need to tell everyone else about it.  she said that she wished she had my boobs b/c then he would b fabulous and i told him that he was fabulous already.    it was really funny.  there is more to this story and mike if ur reading this the rest of the story involves u so ask me about it if i 4get to tell u.  

during intermission we went and looked at the remaining prizes.  there was 3 more vibrators and i said that tammy should win either the glow-in-the-dark one or the thickest one.  all of them except the glow-in-the-dark one (which was 10") were shorter than mine (they were 7" and mine is 7 1/2").  then i said that kayla (since she was going to b wit her bf in a hotel again) should win either the scented bath salts or the boobie pops for tim he he he.  she wanted the fuzzy cuffs *wink, wink*.  well as the show came near the end they wound up auctioning off the glow-in-the-dark vibrator and the fuzzy cuffs.  then the other vibrator that i said tammy should win she won. it was hilarious b/c as soon as the number was called i knew it was hers so i screamed so loud and then she realized it.  she went up there and ashley definitely asked her if that was here girlfriend that was screaming and i yelled it's just me and she was like oh it's the freshman.  then at the end of the show they were just trying to get rid of the rest of the prizes so they were pretty much just throwing them out literally.  when they came to the boobie pops ashley called kalya out and said that she deserved them b/c she had wonderful boobs.

one of the funniest things happened 2night and the story actually requires some background so here it goes:

2yrs. ago i wasn't really feeling the "Christmas Spirit" more so than usual.  it was after my dad was on this whole "real tree" kick and i told him i didn't want a tree 4 Christmas.  he decided that he was going to mix up the holidays and he turned Christmas into an "easter egg hunt."  he told me that my presents were hidden around the house and i had 2 find them.  i was finding them fairly easy and whenever i found a new one i would take some time to look at it and then move on.  i wound up getting a crap load of stuff.  well anywayz he had told me that there was one present that i would never find.  i pestered him and pestered him and finally he went to take a nap and he told me that he would tell/show me where it was when he woke up.  of course he didn't and i never found the mysterious "last present."  my aunt (who was there at the time) and sometimes my dad have held this over my head saying that there has been "something" out there.  

so now here it is 2yrs. later and i was talking to my dad about my new years plans of going to NY.  he was asking what we (tammy, kayla and me) would do there.  i told him prolly just hang out mayb do a lil shopping even though tammy would b the only 1 wit money...unless kayla had some b/c i was broke.  and then he says, but u have a little Christmas money don't u??  i look at him very puzzled and tell him that i only got 3 presents (c previous entry).  i go on 2 tell him that i know i will b getting some money from some other ppl, but i haven't seen them yet.  he tells me that i have another present and to follow him into the kitchen.  he starts rambling about how i have to watch him around the holidays b/c he starts hiding stuff.  then he asks me if it was last year or 2yrs. ago that he hid my presents and i tell him 2.  he starts looking in the cupboards and all around the kitchen.  he says that he put something somewhere 4 me.  we have these three glass container that are three sizes: small, medium, and large.  he opens the smallest one and inside is some money rolled up and tied with white rope and a label on it that says to shaundra.  

i literally died of laughter.  i asked him if it had been there 4 2yrs. and he said he does know (or rather he wouldn't tell me).  we started talking and i said that i was glad that i found/received this now rather than then and he said that i didn't find it so he takes it and tells me 2 close my eyes while he hides it again.  i close my eyes and he hides it.  now the funny thing is he hid it in the microwave...the microwave...who can't hear a microwave when u open it??  anywayz, when i find it he starts jumping around with excitement asking me how i found it and pretty much just being an idiot.  i was frickin' hilarious.
